-- India's REC raises 15.15 bln rupees via 7-yr bonds-sources
-- By Neha Dasgupta and Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Mon Jul 14, 2014 04:48AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, July 14 (Reuters) - India's Rural Electrification Corp (REC) <RURL.NS>, a state-run power sector lender, raised 15.15 billion rupees ($252.25 million) via 7-year bonds at 9.40 percent, three sources familiar with the deal said on Monday.

